        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Here we address why the proposed sensitivity/resolution requirements are necessary and why the suggested compact-array observation is not needed:

1. Data of the same source had been acquired by the SMA, which is comparable to the ALMA compact array, as shown in Fig. 2 &amp; 3. So compact-array observation is not needed.

2. We propose for one ALMA pointing centered at the peak of the SMA map (Fig. 2, right panel). The 2.3 mJy desired sensitivity is 1/10 of the peak intensity estimated from the SMA data.

3. The 0.2" angular resolution is needed for probing mpc scales (the scale of disc formation and of the theoretical prediction of decoupling) at the distance of NGC 2024.

4. Based on the VCS theory (see Method), velocity resolution comparable to thermal line width is needed. This is how the frequency resolution is required.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
